Launched in 1940, the striking car was created by experts in an attempt to overcome fuel shortages during World War Two.

Powered by six batteries, it has a capacity
 of 100 amps at 72 volts - reaching a top speed of just 24mph, with a 
range of 50 miles.

It also features a tubular chassis, an electric motor, front hydraulic brakes and a chain on the rear wheel axis.

Despite being put into production, only 25 models were created due to the limited supply of materials during the war.

